Final variables
1. these are constants, once value is assigned, we cannot change them.
2. Final variable names are written in capital
3. Final variables can be initialized in 3 ways:
    1. when the variable is declared
    2. We can initialize it inside a static block
    3. we can initialize them inside the constructor
        if using this method, then we have to initialize it in every constructor

Final Methods
1. Final method cannot be over ridden in the child class

Final Classes
1. A final class cannot be extended / inherited.